body:
https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/fdeef3ed1809aa9bd4ea9ff0fad92010c6de669c/compiler/rustc_llvm/build.rs#L286

When build rust 1.69.0 with static llvm 16 or llvm15, it will fail like:
"librustc_driver-.....so: undefined reference to `llvm::DOTGraphTraits<llvm::RegionNode*>::getNodeLabel[abi:cxx11](llvm::RegionNode*, llvm::RegionNode*)'"

After digging the build process, I find the undefined symbol is referred by libPolly.a and defined in libLLVMAnalysis.a.
And the --debug output showed that Polly is linked with dylib while LLVMAnalysis linked with static.
So here is the patch to fix this issue.

```rust
--- rustc-1.69.0/compiler/rustc_llvm/build.rs.orig    2023-04-25 09:45:38.469356829 +0800
+++ rustc-1.69.0/compiler/rustc_llvm/build.rs 2023-04-25 09:47:22.144017554 +0800
@@ -282,7 +282,7 @@
             continue;
         }
 
-        let kind = if name.starts_with("LLVM") { llvm_kind } else { "dylib" };
+        let kind = if name.starts_with("LLVM") { llvm_kind } else if name.starts_with("Polly") { llvm_kind } else { "dylib" };
         println!("cargo:rustc-link-lib={kind}={name}");
     }
 
```
